# ================================================
# QUICK START INSTRUCTIONS
# ================================================
# 1. Copy this template:
#    cp .env.template .env
#
# 2. Add your API keys to the .env file:
#    nano .env  # or use your preferred editor
#
# 3. Ensure .env is not tracked by git:
#    git status  # Should NOT show .env file
#
# 4. Run the migration script (if upgrading from config.txt):
#    python migrate_api_keys.py
#
# ================================================
# NOTES
# ================================================
# - API keys in this file override those in config.txt
# - Environment variables override both .env and config.txt
# - Keep this file secure and never share it
# - Most local model APIs don't require API keys
# - You only need to fill in keys for services you use
# ================================================